race.comment: YONGTAI (7) on top. Her last start effort when second at Wodonga as a $3.20 chance is the best recent bit of form in this field, getting back in the field there and finding the line strongly. Gets a middle draw here and should prove very hard to hold out. She ran past MISS HIMALAYA (8) at Wodonga who was up on speed, boxing on for third. She's got versatility and can look to be positive again from the low gate which will suit. JINGU EXPRESS (12) was a bit flat as favourite last time but had been good fresh and can improve. WARLIST (10) finished midfield when resuming from a spell last start over 1200m at Wodonga. Steps up in distance today and can contest for a place.
